Garrha micromita is a moth in the family Oecophoridae. It was described by Turner in 1946. It is found in Australia, where it has been recorded from Queensland.The wingspan is about 20 mm. The forewings are whitish-ochreous with grey irroration forming obscure lines and streaks on and between the veins. The stigmata is minute, the first discal spot at one-third, the plical beneath it and the second discal at two-thirds. The hindwings are whitish.